    "Starting with a particular instance in a chain, we can infer other instances by following the links along the entire chain.",
    "Consequently, exploring object properties among instances along the entire chain helps reveal implicit semantic relationships, which can effectively(4) Sim attr � I x, I y � = ∑ p i∈N AttrSim p i � I x, I y � N,contribute to computing semantic similarity between instances.",
    "For example, in the considered Movie domain ontology, it is important to note that tracing any movie, as illustrated in, using any of its object properties could lead to the discovery of new movies that may share common information (i.e., data and object properties).As an example, the similarity between \"The Good Dinosaur\" with \"Rio2\" movies is computed by comparing their datatype and object properties.",
    "Regarding the datatype property, the two movies are compared by comparing their values of each datatype property using Formula 4.",
